  "text": "levels with different energy, which is essential for coherent operations via Rabi oscillation. Therefore, direct interfacing that admits the energy exchange between different qubits is not allowed. Meanwhile, in order to couple long distance qubits, a photonic quantum bus for topological qubits is of significant importance, where errors from these hybrid architectures can be corrected for a much higher threshold (\u03b5 ~ 0.14) [CITATION_1] 35 , which has already been achieved 36 . However, for topological qubits couple to a cavity mode, only the induced energy shift, due to the large energy mismatch effect, has been investigated before [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
